# GitHub Deployment Rules for Kursfind AI-APP

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js application (Kursfind AI-APP) that needs to be deployed and maintained on GitHub with proper version control practices.

## Repository Setup

### Initial GitHub Setup
1. Create a new repository on GitHub (public or private)
2. Do NOT initialize with README, .gitignore, or license (we have our own)
3. Copy the repository URL for later use

### Local Git Initialization
```bash
# Initialize git repository (if not already done)
git init

# Add all files
git add .

# Create initial commit
git commit -m "Initial commit: Kursfind AI-APP Next.js application"

# Add remote repository
git remote add origin <your-github-repo-url>

# Push to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

## Environment Variables Management

### Security Rules
- NEVER commit `.env` files to GitHub
- Always use `.env.local` for local development
- Store production secrets in Vercel/deployment platform

### Required Environment Variables
Document all required environment variables in a `.env.example` file:
```bash
# API Keys
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# Database
DATABASE_URL=

# Authentication
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=
NEXTAUTH_URL=

# Add other variables as needed
```

## Branch Strategy

### Main Branches
- `main` - Production-ready code
- `develop` - Development branch for integration
- `feature/*` - Feature branches
- `bugfix/*` - Bug fix branches
- `hotfix/*` - Urgent production fixes

### Workflow
1. Create feature branch from `develop`
2. Work on feature
3. Create Pull Request to `develop`
4. After testing, merge `develop` to `main`
5. Deploy `main` to production

## Commit Message Guidelines

### Format
```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

### Types
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `style`: Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
- `refactor`: Code refactoring
- `test`: Adding tests
- `chore`: Build process or auxiliary tool changes
- `perf`: Performance improvements

### Examples
```bash
git commit -m "feat(courses): add course detail page with AI recommendations"
git commit -m "fix(api): resolve CORS issue in course endpoint"
git commit -m "docs(readme): update deployment instructions"
```

## Files to Exclude from Git

### Already in .gitignore
- `node_modules/`
- `.next/`
- `.env` and `.env.local`
- `out/`
- `build/`
- `.DS_Store`
- `*.log`

### Verify Exclusions
Before committing, always check:
```bash
git status
```

## Pre-Deployment Checklist

### Before Pushing to GitHub
- [ ] Remove all console.logs (or use proper logging)
- [ ] Remove commented-out code
- [ ] Ensure no hardcoded secrets or API keys
- [ ] Test build locally: `npm run build`
- [ ] Check for linting errors: `npm run lint`
- [ ] Update documentation if needed
- [ ] Verify `.env.example` is up to date

### Build Verification
```bash
# Test production build locally
npm run build
npm run start

# Check for build errors
# Verify all pages load correctly
```

## Deployment Platforms

### Vercel (Recommended for Next.js)

#### Setup Steps
1. Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com)
2. Sign in with GitHub
3. Import your repository
4. Configure project:
   - Framework Preset: Next.js
   - Root Directory: `./`
   - Build Command: `npm run build`
   - Output Directory: `.next`
5. Add environment variables in Vercel dashboard
6. Deploy

#### Automatic Deployments
- Every push to `main` → Production deployment
- Every PR → Preview deployment
- Configure in Vercel dashboard

### GitHub Actions (CI/CD)

#### Create Workflow File
Location: `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`

```yaml
name: Deploy to Production

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      
      - name: Setup Node.js
        uses: actions/setup-node@v3
        with:
          node-version: '18'
          cache: 'npm'
      
      - name: Install dependencies
        run: npm ci
      
      - name: Lint
        run: npm run lint
      
      - name: Build
        run: npm run build
        env:
          NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL: ${{ secrets.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL }}
      
      - name: Run tests (if available)
        run: npm test --if-present
```

